  "agbContent": "AGB BackQuest 1\r\n\r\nGeneral Terms and Conditions\r\n\r\n1. General Information and Scope\r\n1.1 BackQuest GbR develops and operates the website www.backquest.online (hereinafter referred to as \"Website\") as well as the mobile application \"BackQuest App\" (hereinafter referred to as \"App\"). BackQuest offers registered users guided fitness exercises for the prevention of back pain, improvement of mobility, and relaxation (hereinafter referred to as \"Courses\") through the App. \"Users\" are defined as all natural persons who use the Website, the App, and/or the Courses offered therein. 1.2 These General Terms and Conditions (hereinafter referred to as \"GTC\") in their current version at the time of the contract conclusion apply to the entire range of services provided by the provider. 1.3 Deviating or supplementary terms and conditions of the user do not become part of the contract unless the provider explicitly agrees to their applicability in writing. These GTC also apply if the provider executes services unconditionally despite being aware of contradictory or deviating conditions of the user unless the provider has explicitly agreed to this in writing.\r\n2. User's Health Condition\r\n2.1 The use of the coaching sessions requires a stable general state of health. The user assures to meet this requirement. 2.2 The offerings of BackQuest and the Courses are not intended to provide medical advice or diagnosis and do not replace a doctor's visit. The goal of the App is to raise awareness of health issues and motivate users to engage in more movement and relaxation. 2.3 Users who require or have received medical or therapeutic diagnoses or treatments, as well as pregnant women, must consult their doctor or therapist before using the Courses. 2.4 The use of the Courses is at the user's own risk. If the user experiences pain or discomfort during or after the application of the Courses, they should stop the Course immediately and consult a doctor.\r\n\r\nAGB BackQuest 2\r\n\r\n3. BackQuest Offerings\r\n3.1 The provider's Courses are offered via an interactive, software-based application for online-supported prevention of back pain. The App provides individually tailored videos that users can complete in a predetermined sequence. Additionally, users can read the accompanying text-based information to learn more about the scientific background of the training. 3.2 The provider continuously develops the software and its content. In doing so, new features may be introduced, existing features replaced with new ones, or removed without replacement.\r\n4. Registration and Use\r\n4.1 The possibility of using the App begins with installation. The currently available beta version can be used free of charge by all users. 4.2 Use requires the creation of a user account. Such a user account may not be transferred to third parties. The provider reserves the right to verify the data provided during registration through appropriate measures. 4.3 By confirming the registration, a contract for the use of the provider's services is concluded between the provider and the user. 4.4 Registration requires that the user is either 18 years old or has the express consent of their legal guardian.\r\n5. Right of Withdrawal\r\n5.1 Users who are consumers within the meaning of Section 13 of the German Civil Code (BGB) have a statutory right of withdrawal. 5.2 A consumer is any natural person who concludes a legal transaction for purposes that are predominantly neither commercial nor self-employed (§ 13 BGB).\r\n\r\nAGB BackQuest 3\r\n\r\n6. Right of Withdrawal\r\n6.1 If a BackQuest product has been purchased for a fee, the user has a right of withdrawal. You have the right to withdraw from this contract within fourteen days without giving any reason. The withdrawal period is fourteen days from the date of contract conclusion. To exercise your right of withdrawal, you must inform us by means of a clear statement (e.g., a letter sent by post, fax, or email) of your decision to withdraw from this contract. You may use the attached sample withdrawal form, but it is not mandatory. 6.2 To meet the withdrawal deadline, it is sufficient for you to send your communication regarding your exercise of the right of withdrawal before the withdrawal period has expired. 6.3 Your right of withdrawal expires prematurely if we have fully performed the service and only began performing the service after you, as a consumer, gave your express consent and at the same time confirmed your knowledge that you would lose your right of withdrawal upon full performance of the contract by us. 6.4 Consequences of withdrawal: If you withdraw from this contract, we will reimburse you all payments we have received from you, without undue delay and at the latest within fourteen days from the day on which we receive the notification of your withdrawal from this contract. For this reimbursement, we will use the same means of payment that you used for the initial transaction, unless expressly agreed otherwise with you; in no case will you be charged fees for this reimbursement. If you requested that the services commence during the withdrawal period, you shall pay us a reasonable amount proportionate to the services performed until the point at which you informed us of your withdrawal regarding this contract, in comparison to the full coverage of the services provided for in the contract. If our services have been free of charge so far, you are not entitled to a refund.\r\n\r\nAGB BackQuest 4\r\n\r\n6.5 Sample Withdrawal Form (If you want to withdraw from the contract, please fill out this form and return it.) BackQuest GbR, Gärtnerweg 62, 60322 Frankfurt, hallo@backquest.online I/we (*) hereby revoke the contract concluded by me/us (*) for the purchase of the following goods: (*) / the provision of the following service: (*) Ordered on ______________() / received on ______________() Name of consumer(s) ______________ Address of consumer(s) _______________ (only if notification is made on paper) Date _______________ (*) Delete as applicable. As an online business, the provider is obliged to inform consumers about the European Commission's Online Dispute Resolution (ODR) platform. This ODR platform is accessible via the following link: Online Dispute Resolution | European Commission. However, the provider does not participate in dispute resolution proceedings before a consumer arbitration board. The provider does not store the contract text.",
  "dataPrivacy": "Datenschutzerklärung",
  "dataPrivacyContent": "Data Privacy Statement\r\n\r\nBackQuest 1\r\n\r\nPrivacy Policy for Using the BackQuest App\r\nThis privacy policy of BackQuest GbR aims to inform you comprehensively as a user of our BackQuest App about how we process personal data. Protecting your privacy is of utmost importance to us, which is why compliance with legal data protection regulations is a matter of course for us. This privacy policy does not apply to data processing on our website. The applicable privacy policy for that can be found at any time at: https://backquest.online/privacy-policy/\r\nContact Information of the Data Controller\r\nIf you have questions or suggestions regarding this information or wish to exercise your rights, please contact: BackQuest GbR Gärtnerweg 62 60322 Frankfurt, Germany\r\nData Protection Officer\r\nIf you have questions about our data protection measures or the processing of your data, you can contact our Data Protection Officer at: datenschutz@backquest.online\r\nProcessing of Personal Data\r\nPersonal data refers to all information about a specific or identifiable person. When using the BackQuest App, the following personal data is processed:\r\n• Email address/Username\r\n• Gender and Age\r\n• Height and Weight\r\n• Activity Level\r\n• Previous Sports Experience and Goals\r\n• Training Data (Completed Exercises, Feedback on Exercises)\r\nAfter consent, anonymized usage data from various aspects is collected during app usage. The subsequent analysis of usage data is carried out exclusively in anonymized form.\r\n\r\nBackQuest Privacy Policy 2\r\n\r\nPurpose of Processing\r\nWe process your personal data only to the extent necessary for conducting the prevention training. All collected data serves to (1) provide our users with the best possible training experience, (2) address your needs, and (3) ensure the continuous technical functionality.\r\nLegal Basis for Data Processing\r\nWe process personal data only in compliance with data protection regulations (GDPR and BDSG). Data processing occurs only after explicit consent (§ 25 Abs. 1 TTDSG or Art. 6 Abs. 1 lit. a GDPR), to fulfill contractual measures (Art. 6 Abs. 1 lit. b GDPR), due to a legal obligation (Art. 6 Abs. 1 lit. c GDPR), or under the respective special legal provision (Art. 6 Abs. 1 lit. d, e, or f GDPR).\r\nStorage Duration and Deletion of Data\r\nUnless otherwise indicated in this privacy policy, we store your data only as long as necessary. Your personal data will be deleted as soon as it is no longer required for its intended purpose, unless legal retention periods apply. Final deletion occurs after the expiration of these retention periods. If you wish for us to delete your data, you can send an email at any time to datenschutz@backquest.online.\r\n\r\nBackQuest Privacy Policy 3\r\n\r\nData Recipients\r\nPersonal data processed in connection with the use of the BackQuest App is generally not shared with third parties unless necessary for a specific purpose. We ensure adequate security measures to prevent unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction of the data. For data processing, we collaborate with the following service providers who have access to your data.\r\nOVH Cloud\r\nWe store and process your health-related personal data exclusively using the cloud service or cloud infrastructure of OVH (OVH SAS Group, 2 Rue Kellermann, 59100 Roubaix, France; hereinafter referred to as \"OVH\") for IT services and secure storage or secure exchange of digital content and information. All data is processed exclusively in Germany. Further information from OVH on data protection can be found at: https://www.ovhcloud.com/de/personal-data-protection/\r\nGoogle Firebase\r\nWe use Google Firebase (a service of Google Ireland Limited, Gordon House, Barrow Street, Dublin 4, Ireland) to send push notifications, for example. No tracking via Firebase is conducted. Further information can be found at: https://firebase.google.com/support/privacy?hl=en\r\nData Processing to Improve Usability\r\nBackQuest regularly conducts user satisfaction surveys. If you have agreed, you will receive invitations to questionnaires, individual, or group interviews where you can voluntarily share your experiences using the app and contribute to its development.\r\n\r\nBackQuest Privacy Policy 4\r\n\r\nCondens\r\nWe use Condens by Condens Insights GmbH (Brienner Str. 41, 80333 Munich) to analyze data on usability. With your consent, your app usage experiences and suggestions for improving the app are processed, structured, and visualized in anonymized form. These are only associated with general demographic profile information. More information about the provider can be found at: https://condens.io/gdpr/\r\nBrevo (formerly SendinBlue)\r\nWe use Brevo (formerly SendinBlue) by Sendinblue GmbH (Köpenicker Straße 127, 10179 Berlin, Germany) to send our newsletter and measure open and click rates. If you agree to participate in our user surveys, we forward your email address to Brevo. Additionally, the meetings and online sessions of user surveys are conducted via the provider’s meeting function. More information about the provider can be found at: https://www.brevo.com/en/privacy-policy/\r\nYour Rights\r\nAs a data subject, you have various rights regarding your personal data. You have the right to access information about your data (Art. 15 GDPR and § 34 BDSG) and can contact us at any time to exercise this right (Art. 16 GDPR). If you make a request for information that is not in writing, we may require proof to ensure that you are the person concerned. Additionally, you have the right to correct or delete your data (Art. 17 GDPR and § 35 BDSG) and to restrict processing (Art. 18 GDPR) as far as legally permissible. You have the right to object to the processing of your personal data under the statutory conditions. You can withdraw your consent to the processing of your data at any time (Art. 7 Abs. 3 GDPR). Moreover, under Art. 20 GDPR, you have the right to data portability in accordance with data protection regulations.\r\n\r\nBackQuest Privacy Policy 5\r\n\r\nRight to Lodge a Complaint with a Supervisory Authority\r\nIf you have concerns or complaints about the processing of your personal data, you can contact a data protection supervisory authority in accordance with Art. 77 GDPR.\r\nChanges to This Privacy Policy\r\nThis privacy policy may be updated in the event of changes in data processing or other occasions. The current version is available at any time on our website. We hope this information gives you a better understanding of how we protect and use your data. If you have questions, feel free to contact us anytime.\r\nLast updated: 20.02.2024",
